The man died from variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob (vCJD) disease in Texas in May 2014, 18 months after he first showed symptoms .
The extreme rarity of the disease led the man to be misdiagnosed with psychiatric symptoms before he moved to the U.S. in the 1990s .
He'd lived in Kuwait, Russia and Lebanon where all three previously documented victims of vCJD in the United Kingdom had lived previously .